snippet.textDisplay: All organisms mutate. In the presence of oxidizing agents like oxygen, natural UV radiation, and errors in DNA/RNA replication. The only way a mutated version could over take the wild type version is if  they outcompete (replicate faster, become more stable etc). Most mutations will either have no effect or will destabilize that version of the virus, causing it to be outcompeted by the naturally occurring version. Either way your body is very good at attacking and recognizing foreign RNA species. So unless you are immunocompromised you will recover.

snippet.textDisplay: Meanwhile there are possibly hundreds of thousands of undocumented cases of people with this virus. The Dr.'s just call it "flu-like symptoms"...
